The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Union Bank of India has reduced interest rates on home loans of up to Rs 30 lakh by 0.5-1 per cent, depending on the tenure and type of loan. The Reserve Bank in its annual monetary policy had provided a low risk weightage of 50 per cent on home loans of up to Rs 30 lakh. Union Bank will charge a lesser rate of interest on home loans sanctioned on or after May 9, the bank said here in a release.                             
	 HCL Infosystems has acquired Natural Technologies Pvt Ltd. The acquisition will strengthen HCLs range of offerings to the banking, financial services and insurance (BFSI) sector. HCL will develop the banking facility at Jaipur into a centre of excellence, which will build products for the co-operative and rural banking and the emerging financial inclusion sector.                             
	 Universal Cables Ltd has registered the highest ever turnover of Rs. 562.96 crore in fiscal 2007-08, which represents a year on year growth of 30 per cent. The net profit was lower at Rs. 17.26 crore compared with Rs. 21.97 crore in the previous year. Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortisation increased to Rs. 54.88 crore from Rs. 48.86 crore in the previous year.                            
	 National Petroleum Construction Company (NPCC) of Abu Dhabi has entered into a joint venture agreement with Arcadia Shipping Ltd of India to form NPCC Engineering Ltd (NEL). NPCC recorded a turnover of $2 billion last year. NPCC will have a 74 per cent stake in the joint venture and Arcadia will hold the rest.                             
	 Fidelity Fund Management has entered into an agreement with Federal Bank for the distribution of its product. Fidelitys mutual funds will now be available at more than 600 branches of Federal Bank throughout the country.                             
	 Unity Infraprojects Ltd has bagged two orders worth Rs 223 crore. The company will be constructing regulated environmental buildings at the prison complex, at Mandoli in Delhi for Rs 154.29 crore. The workwill be completed within 30 months.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
